# .gitignore — kyleturner/dotfiles
# This file is the actual enforcement mechanism for "no secrets in a public repo."
# Everything under it is either a resolved secret, a machine-specific artifact, or
# cache/state that shouldn't be version-controlled. See macos-dev-workstation-ARCHIVE.md
# Section 4.8 for the full reasoning — *.tpl files are safe and committed; their
# resolved output (listed below) is never committed.

# --- Resolved secrets (op inject output — never the source, always the output) ---
# The .tpl versions of these ARE committed and safe (op:// references only).
dot_config/secrets/.env.global
.env.local
.env.local.*
!.env.local.tpl
!*.env.*.tpl

# --- chezmoi state ---
.chezmoistate.boltdb
.chezmoi.toml
!.chezmoi.toml.tmpl

# --- macOS junk ---
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes

# --- Editor/IDE local state ---
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# --- Logs ---
*.log
bootstrap.log

# --- 1Password / age keys, if ever introduced despite the op-inject-only design ---
*.key
key.txt
